1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:01,770
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,770 --> 00:00:03,410
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,480 --> 00:00:05,240
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,750 --> 00:00:08,080
(Episode 22)

5
00:00:17,690 --> 00:00:19,220
Jung Ran, please.

6
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:22,330
What are you doing here
after all that drama with her?

7
00:00:22,790 --> 00:00:23,960
I'm here to see Ms. Choi.

8
00:00:24,930 --> 00:00:27,430
Why? So you can grab her
by the hair again?

9
00:00:28,130 --> 00:00:30,840
Forget her hair.
Today, I'm seizing an opportunity.

10
00:00:31,040 --> 00:00:33,140
Sure, do whatever you want.

11
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:36,210
Just please don't start a fight, okay?

12
00:00:36,610 --> 00:00:38,580
You think that's all I'm good for?

13
00:00:41,610 --> 00:00:42,910
There she is.

14
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:03,400
Hey, why are you hiding?
I thought you wanted to see her.

15
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:06,870
Now's not the time to meet her.
It's time to hit record.

16
00:01:08,140 --> 00:01:10,280
Quick, point your phone at them.

17
00:01:11,210 --> 00:01:13,810
Here? In the middle of all this?

18
00:01:14,610 --> 00:01:15,780
What am I supposed to do,
take a selfie?

19
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:19,820
Why do I even bother with you?
Give it here.

20
00:01:26,390 --> 00:01:28,130
Why should I fix anything?

21
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:34,130
You were more than happy
to do it for money.

22
00:01:34,830 --> 00:01:37,170
So you're just going to bail on me?

23
00:01:38,740 --> 00:01:40,670
If I get caught
by the police or Adele,

24
00:01:40,670 --> 00:01:42,640
do you think
you'll get away scot-free?

25
00:01:43,140 --> 00:01:44,680
So just...

26
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:48,310
lay low.

27
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:52,520
Then pay up.

28
00:01:53,350 --> 00:01:56,150
Everything costs money
when you're in hiding.

29
00:01:57,020 --> 00:01:58,020
A hundred grand should do it.

30
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:00,930
What, 100,000 dollars?

31
00:02:00,930 --> 00:02:03,260
Move fast,
or become a jobless criminal.

32
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:06,030
You don't want me
to say "screw this," get caught,

33
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:09,530
and spill everything.

34
00:02:32,820 --> 00:02:34,260
Well, now.

35
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:39,930
Looks like I stumbled upon
something interesting.

36
00:03:11,930 --> 00:03:12,930
Are you okay?

37
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:20,670
I'm suddenly not feeling very well.

38
00:03:21,610 --> 00:03:22,840
I should get going.

39
00:03:34,290 --> 00:03:38,120
Dad!

40
00:03:38,890 --> 00:03:40,830
Dad!

41
00:03:42,890 --> 00:03:43,900
Chloe?

42
00:03:48,430 --> 00:03:49,470
Dad.

43
00:03:50,300 --> 00:03:54,040
Yes, Dad's right here. It's okay.

44
00:03:54,510 --> 00:03:55,810
You don't have to worry anymore.

45
00:04:04,350 --> 00:04:06,320
This whole thing
has been very stressful for Chloe.

46
00:04:06,990 --> 00:04:08,550
She was already feeling run-down,

47
00:04:08,550 --> 00:04:10,290
and I guess she suddenly got dizzy.

48
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:14,990
I'll take her to the hospital,
so you can go on ahead.

49
00:04:15,260 --> 00:04:16,890
I'll come with you, then.

50
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:18,760
Why?

51
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,160
Sorry?

52
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:22,100
You're not her next of kin
or her friend, so why?

53
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:25,870
Well...

54
00:04:26,270 --> 00:04:28,510
We'll be on our way, then.

55
00:04:29,870 --> 00:04:30,880
Let's go.

56
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,470
What did you just say?

57
00:05:01,170 --> 00:05:02,170
A deal?

58
00:05:05,140 --> 00:05:07,580
Why did I even consider you
for my son...

59
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:11,320
when I would've usually thought
this was ridiculous?

60
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:17,190
What else would I want
besides your family's stocks?

61
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:20,090
The only reason I'd help you now...

62
00:05:20,430 --> 00:05:22,630
is for that exact reason.
Am I wrong?

63
00:05:23,630 --> 00:05:26,360
If I hand over those stocks,
I'll have nothing left.

64
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:29,230
You're asking for everything I have.

65
00:05:29,530 --> 00:05:31,500
How can I give that away?

66
00:05:41,010 --> 00:05:44,420
See? Here we go again
with the fighting and hair-pulling.

67
00:05:47,450 --> 00:05:48,450
Listen.

68
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:50,790
Do you still not get it?

69
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:55,560
If this deal falls through,
who do you think I'll go to next?

70
00:05:56,790 --> 00:05:58,230
Are you threatening me?

71
00:05:58,230 --> 00:05:59,760
Of course I am.

72
00:06:00,230 --> 00:06:02,900
I'm a master at making threats.

73
00:06:03,940 --> 00:06:04,940
So,

74
00:06:05,340 --> 00:06:08,870
should I run to the chairman
and show him the video I took?

75
00:06:08,870 --> 00:06:09,970
Or...

76
00:06:10,780 --> 00:06:14,710
should I help you
and make this whole mess go away?

77
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:21,450
Let go of me first.

78
00:06:23,190 --> 00:06:24,960
How would you make it go away?

79
00:06:37,370 --> 00:06:39,040
You should've seen a doctor.

80
00:06:40,340 --> 00:06:42,770
All they'll do
is prescribe medicine for me.

81
00:06:44,580 --> 00:06:47,680
If I'd known, I would've made sure
you finished treatment first.

82
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:54,220
The acrid,

83
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:56,520
burning smell.

84
00:06:59,290 --> 00:07:00,930
The scorching heat,

85
00:07:01,790 --> 00:07:03,530
the flickering flames...

86
00:07:06,100 --> 00:07:08,400
The moment my dad died,

87
00:07:09,470 --> 00:07:10,470
that...

88
00:07:12,700 --> 00:07:13,940
fear...

89
00:07:15,970 --> 00:07:17,680
can never be...

90
00:07:18,180 --> 00:07:20,210
completely cured.

91
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:24,080
This pain in my heart?

92
00:07:25,420 --> 00:07:27,420
I don't think it'll go away...

93
00:07:28,650 --> 00:07:30,020
until I clear my father's name.

94
00:07:38,330 --> 00:07:40,830
When I let you take
my daughter's name,

95
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:44,300
I was grieving my child...

96
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:46,370
who went missing
on that frozen mountain,

97
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:50,410
aching inside, unable to bring myself
to declare her dead.

98
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:53,880
Jin Ju,

99
00:07:54,780 --> 00:07:56,310
I promised I'd think of you
as my daughter too.

100
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:03,290
Clearing Dr. Baek's name
is important,

101
00:08:03,990 --> 00:08:06,660
but I'm more worried about you...

102
00:08:06,860 --> 00:08:09,490
getting hurt and struggling.

103
00:08:10,660 --> 00:08:13,160
You could be framed like this,

104
00:08:13,230 --> 00:08:15,300
or you could end up
in even greater danger.

105
00:08:15,830 --> 00:08:17,000
Don't worry.

106
00:08:17,870 --> 00:08:19,670
No matter what they throw at me,

107
00:08:21,540 --> 00:08:23,010
I won't lose.

108
00:08:25,780 --> 00:08:27,380
All right. Good.

109
00:08:29,410 --> 00:08:30,410
Still,

110
00:08:31,250 --> 00:08:32,980
you have to be careful.

111
00:08:33,650 --> 00:08:35,150
Always.

112
00:08:39,660 --> 00:08:40,660
I will.

113
00:08:43,160 --> 00:08:45,030
Okay, good.

114
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:49,400
Anyway,

115
00:08:50,330 --> 00:08:52,170
what about Park Min Jun?

116
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:55,670
From what he saw,
he'll think you're afraid of fire.

117
00:08:56,370 --> 00:08:57,440
What if...

118
00:08:57,710 --> 00:09:00,780
he connects it to the explosion
from the past?

119
00:09:02,610 --> 00:09:03,610
I'll just say...

120
00:09:04,580 --> 00:09:07,390
I was caught in a fire in the US.

121
00:09:08,590 --> 00:09:12,020
He might get more suspicious
if I try to hide my fear of fire.

122
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:15,190
If he's still suspicious
even after that,

123
00:09:15,690 --> 00:09:17,800
we'll figure something out then.

124
00:09:20,130 --> 00:09:22,170
Okay, let's do that.

125
00:09:53,660 --> 00:09:54,670
Chloe?

126
00:09:56,630 --> 00:09:57,700
I was wondering...

127
00:09:58,700 --> 00:10:00,270
about Baek Jin Ju.

128
00:10:02,210 --> 00:10:03,640
Is there anything
unique about her...

129
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:06,880
that sets her apart from Chloe?

130
00:10:08,910 --> 00:10:10,350
Chloe's reaction to the fire.

131
00:10:11,950 --> 00:10:14,450
The explosion and Jin Ju.

132
00:10:16,190 --> 00:10:17,360
Am I...

133
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,760
grasping at straws again?

134
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:30,840
(Adele)

135
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:32,100
(Plagiarized designs! Chloe, out!)

136
00:10:32,170 --> 00:10:33,470
(Are designs a joke?
Step down, you plagiarist!)

137
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:44,280
Look, it's Chloe!

138
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:46,020
- It's Chloe!
- There she is.

139
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,590
What's your response
to the plagiarism allegations?

140
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:49,420
Didn't you fake
your consulting success?

141
00:10:49,420 --> 00:10:51,290
What else are you lying about?

142
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,360
Chloe!

143
00:10:52,990 --> 00:10:55,560
What do you have to say
about his design book?

144
00:10:56,290 --> 00:10:57,830
What's the deal
with the design book?

145
00:10:59,530 --> 00:11:00,600
Excuse me.

146
00:11:03,430 --> 00:11:05,800
Chloe is the victim
in this incident.

147
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:09,140
The plagiarism claim
was a blatant lie,

148
00:11:10,340 --> 00:11:12,410
and the design book
he used as evidence...

149
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:14,650
was actually stolen from Chloe.

150
00:11:15,650 --> 00:11:17,820
Now that a police investigation
has started,

151
00:11:18,820 --> 00:11:21,150
we ask that you refrain
from any speculative reporting.

152
00:11:23,050 --> 00:11:24,060
Let's go.

153
00:11:26,260 --> 00:11:27,630
- Excuse me!
- Just a moment!

154
00:11:27,690 --> 00:11:29,230
- Coming through.
- About the plagiarism...

155
00:11:29,530 --> 00:11:31,200
Was anything else taken?

156
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:33,860
- Coming through.
- Please say something.

157
00:11:34,530 --> 00:11:36,530
I'll send out the press release
right away.

158
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:38,300
No.

159
00:11:39,040 --> 00:11:42,270
Tell them to wait a few more hours
before sending it out.

160
00:11:42,740 --> 00:11:43,740
Yes, sir.

161
00:11:44,580 --> 00:11:48,550
We couldn't frame her
because they found the CCTV footage,

162
00:11:50,180 --> 00:11:52,720
but she still has to pay
for her audacity.

163
00:11:53,420 --> 00:11:54,790
Yes, I understand.

164
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:58,860
Anyway,
once the press release is out,

165
00:11:58,860 --> 00:12:00,090
it'll be revealed...

166
00:12:00,830 --> 00:12:03,460
that there's a thief at Adele Group.

167
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:09,100
No matter how we spin it,
it's a total embarrassment.

168
00:12:10,570 --> 00:12:12,070
The sheer audacity.

169
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:17,310
Who at Adele...

170
00:12:18,140 --> 00:12:20,640
would dare pull a stunt like that?

171
00:12:23,110 --> 00:12:25,620
Who's been acting out of character?

172
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:39,300
What did you want to see me for?

173
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:41,570
I figured...

174
00:12:42,330 --> 00:12:44,240
you'd have something to say.

175
00:12:45,970 --> 00:12:46,970
Sorry?

176
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:51,740
Normally, you'd be pestering me
to let you get married,

177
00:12:51,880 --> 00:12:54,080
no matter what Min Jun says,

178
00:12:54,410 --> 00:12:56,680
and making a fuss
about moving things forward.

179
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:59,650
But you're being awfully quiet.

180
00:13:00,350 --> 00:13:01,590
Is there something...

181
00:13:01,850 --> 00:13:04,020
more important than your wedding?

182
00:13:06,490 --> 00:13:07,490
Well,

183
00:13:08,190 --> 00:13:10,090
the company is dealing
with a major incident.

184
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:14,060
No one would listen
if I brought up my wedding right now.

185
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:15,900
I'm not happy about it,

186
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:19,470
but I was planning to wait
until all of this is over.

187
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:22,670
Is that so?

188
00:13:26,410 --> 00:13:28,450
I see.

189
00:13:28,780 --> 00:13:30,950
Speaking of which,

190
00:13:32,550 --> 00:13:34,350
all this happened...

191
00:13:34,350 --> 00:13:37,190
after Min Jun called off
the engagement.

192
00:13:40,090 --> 00:13:41,130
On top of that,

193
00:13:41,830 --> 00:13:44,090
whoever stole the design book...

194
00:13:44,730 --> 00:13:46,100
is apparently an insider.

195
00:13:46,760 --> 00:13:48,000
In this world,

196
00:13:49,630 --> 00:13:51,640
there are no coincidences.

197
00:13:54,970 --> 00:13:57,780
If you're suspecting me,
you're barking up the wrong tree.

198
00:13:58,910 --> 00:13:59,910
Think about it.

199
00:14:00,210 --> 00:14:03,850
I'd be the prime suspect.
Do you think I'd be that foolish?

200
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:07,480
That's true.

201
00:14:08,150 --> 00:14:10,990
You shouldn't have done
something that foolish.

202
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:15,230
Now that Min Jun is refusing
to go through with the wedding,

203
00:14:16,290 --> 00:14:18,060
that kind of trouble
would get you...

204
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:20,930
kicked out of the company
and cost you...

205
00:14:21,570 --> 00:14:22,900
any chance of marrying him.

206
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:29,840
Of course. I'm well aware of that.

207
00:14:30,810 --> 00:14:34,610
Since the police are on it,
I hope it's sorted out soon...

208
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:38,480
so my wedding can get back on track.

209
00:15:11,780 --> 00:15:12,820
It's about our deal.

210
00:15:13,750 --> 00:15:14,890
Let's get it over with.

211
00:15:17,050 --> 00:15:18,060
The shares...

212
00:15:20,990 --> 00:15:22,360
I'll hand them over.

213
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:33,770
I knew
she'd come crawling back eventually.

214
00:15:36,170 --> 00:15:38,740
Will Ms. Choi give up the shares?

215
00:15:39,540 --> 00:15:41,710
She has to save
her own skin first, doesn't she?

216
00:15:43,110 --> 00:15:44,280
Let's proceed as planned.

217
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:46,080
But...

218
00:15:46,550 --> 00:15:48,420
if we go with your plan,

219
00:15:48,820 --> 00:15:51,190
the false accusation
will get cleared up.

220
00:15:52,060 --> 00:15:54,390
Doesn't that mean
we're helping President Kim?

221
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:57,060
Well, will you look at that?

222
00:15:57,460 --> 00:15:59,160
Did the sun rise in the west
this morning?

223
00:16:00,030 --> 00:16:02,700
How did you figure all that out
with that little brain of yours?

224
00:16:02,770 --> 00:16:05,070
It's just a little rusty,
that's all.

225
00:16:05,140 --> 00:16:08,140
When I put my mind to it,
the gears turn just fine.

226
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:12,410
If the gears turn that well,
you'd know why I'm doing this.

227
00:16:14,710 --> 00:16:16,110
This false accusation?

228
00:16:17,850 --> 00:16:21,750
The game was over the moment
Tae Ho got the police involved.

229
00:16:22,750 --> 00:16:26,290
Interfering with Kim Myung Hui now
is just a waste of energy.

230
00:16:27,360 --> 00:16:29,990
Instead, we need
to snatch up the shares...

231
00:16:29,990 --> 00:16:31,830
while she's distracted.

232
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:35,730
In the succession fight,
whoever has the most shares wins.

233
00:16:36,270 --> 00:16:37,770
Which means in the end,

234
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:41,270
I, Oh Jung Ran,
will be the one to win.

235
00:16:43,170 --> 00:16:44,270
At this point,

236
00:16:44,340 --> 00:16:47,480
you practically have a PhD
in scheming.

237
00:16:48,650 --> 00:16:51,450
Not everyone can be
this ruthless, you know.

238
00:16:51,820 --> 00:16:54,020
Only someone like me
could swindle shares...

239
00:16:54,020 --> 00:16:55,250
from that sly fox, Ms. Choi,

240
00:16:55,550 --> 00:16:59,890
and battle that vile witch,
Kim Myung Hui, for 30 years,

241
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:03,360
all while dealing a major blow
to Myung Hui from behind.

242
00:17:12,170 --> 00:17:15,270
It appears the delayed press release
caused an issue.

243
00:17:17,010 --> 00:17:19,510
There's a Korean saying,
"Cause the illness,"

244
00:17:19,840 --> 00:17:21,280
"then sell the cure."

245
00:17:21,980 --> 00:17:24,450
Had you released
the footage yesterday,

246
00:17:25,380 --> 00:17:27,120
none of this would've happened.

247
00:17:29,020 --> 00:17:31,050
You created this problem
by telling me to wait,

248
00:17:31,390 --> 00:17:33,320
and now you're playing the hero
by helping out.

249
00:17:38,430 --> 00:17:41,100
So, no, I don't want to thank you.

250
00:17:41,730 --> 00:17:45,140
I'll repay you for your help
some other way.

251
00:17:57,080 --> 00:17:58,650
Welcome. Please, have a seat.

252
00:18:10,390 --> 00:18:11,700
This is a little overdue,

253
00:18:12,430 --> 00:18:14,470
but congratulations
on becoming president.

254
00:18:16,230 --> 00:18:19,140
I haven't done anything worthy
of congratulations yet.

255
00:18:19,140 --> 00:18:21,040
I should've visited you...

256
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:23,370
rather than asking you
to come all this way.

257
00:18:23,970 --> 00:18:26,510
Wouldn't it sound better to say...

258
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:28,580
you had no choice...

259
00:18:28,580 --> 00:18:30,750
since the matchmaker insisted
on meeting,

260
00:18:31,220 --> 00:18:33,580
rather than visiting
Ihwachae yourself?

261
00:18:36,020 --> 00:18:37,790
I'm always in your debt.

262
00:18:40,090 --> 00:18:43,160
And it seems you need my help again.

263
00:18:44,090 --> 00:18:45,300
Is this about...

264
00:18:46,300 --> 00:18:47,700
the false accusation?

265
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:50,770
The police have begun
an investigation,

266
00:18:50,770 --> 00:18:52,640
so I'm going to see what they find.

267
00:18:53,870 --> 00:18:56,240
Then what can I help you with?

268
00:19:03,080 --> 00:19:04,080
I'm hoping...

269
00:19:04,880 --> 00:19:07,580
to get information
about these two people.

270
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:10,850
(Baek Jin Ju)

271
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:15,230
They are two different people
with the exact same face.

272
00:19:17,260 --> 00:19:19,100
Baek Jin Ju and Chloe.

273
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:20,360
What exactly...

274
00:19:21,030 --> 00:19:23,330
do you want to know?

275
00:19:24,540 --> 00:19:27,140
Whether they might actually be
the same person.

276
00:19:28,110 --> 00:19:32,680
I want to know
if Baek Jin Ju came back as Chloe.

277
00:19:37,950 --> 00:19:40,450
I can't go into the details, but...

278
00:19:42,990 --> 00:19:45,560
You don't have to.

279
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:46,660
However,

280
00:19:47,060 --> 00:19:49,260
I do need to be clear on one thing.

281
00:19:50,860 --> 00:19:54,360
If Baek Jin Ju has returned
as Chloe,

282
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:56,400
is that something...

283
00:19:56,870 --> 00:19:59,840
to celebrate or fear?

284
00:20:07,180 --> 00:20:08,910
It would be a heavy burden.

285
00:20:23,960 --> 00:20:25,900
(Division 1 Director's Office)

286
00:20:30,930 --> 00:20:32,540
Baek Jin Ju...

287
00:20:35,840 --> 00:20:37,810
I understand the weight...

288
00:20:38,510 --> 00:20:40,280
of the emotions she carries...

289
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:43,180
and what she intends to do.

290
00:20:46,450 --> 00:20:49,390
But I intend to bear it.

291
00:20:50,150 --> 00:20:51,990
Whether things turn out
for the best,

292
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:54,290
or for the worst,

293
00:20:55,230 --> 00:20:58,600
I will simply be grateful
that she's alive.

294
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:02,670
Whatever it takes,

295
00:21:02,730 --> 00:21:05,600
I want to do my best to help her.

296
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:11,740
You always carry your burdens
and do your best.

297
00:21:13,380 --> 00:21:17,410
So how could this old woman
not offer her help?

298
00:21:21,650 --> 00:21:24,760
I'll be in touch as soon as
I've looked into it.

299
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:27,390
Thank you.

300
00:21:35,700 --> 00:21:37,130
We've completed our investigation
of the office.

301
00:21:37,970 --> 00:21:40,370
We'll review
the CCTV footage you provided...

302
00:21:40,770 --> 00:21:42,310
and see if we can find any leads.

303
00:21:43,170 --> 00:21:45,480
- We're counting on you.
- All right, then.

304
00:21:51,010 --> 00:21:53,150
I heard there was a commotion
in the lobby this morning.

305
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:54,890
Are you okay?

306
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:57,250
It was nothing.

307
00:21:59,260 --> 00:22:01,120
I should've been there.

308
00:22:01,530 --> 00:22:03,630
If I had taken down
all those reporters,

309
00:22:04,630 --> 00:22:05,960
you would've totally fallen for me.

310
00:22:12,270 --> 00:22:15,810
Now that the police are involved
and it's all over the news,

311
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:18,380
nothing like this will happen again.

312
00:22:21,210 --> 00:22:22,210
Right.

313
00:22:30,950 --> 00:22:32,020
Are you looking...

314
00:22:32,820 --> 00:22:35,890
for someone else again
when I'm right here?

315
00:22:37,030 --> 00:22:39,230
- It's not that...
- Min Jun.

316
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:43,030
He took the day off,
so don't bother waiting for him.

317
00:22:46,100 --> 00:22:47,100
Instead of him,

318
00:22:47,670 --> 00:22:50,670
how about you focus on me?
I'm right here.

319
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:22,540
(Electricity Shutoff Notice,
Gas Service Suspension Notice)

320
00:23:26,980 --> 00:23:30,480
(Credit Information Company,
National Tax Service)

321
00:23:34,580 --> 00:23:36,150
(For the Addressee Only,
Mr. Go Han Su)

322
00:23:36,220 --> 00:23:39,290
(Credit Information Company,
Mr. Go Han Su)

323
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:43,460
He was desperate for money?

324
00:24:07,280 --> 00:24:08,290
What's up?

325
00:24:08,490 --> 00:24:09,820
What gives?

326
00:24:09,820 --> 00:24:12,760
So you decided to start getting paid
for doing nothing?

327
00:24:13,490 --> 00:24:17,160
The office is a total madhouse
with reporters and cops,

328
00:24:17,590 --> 00:24:20,060
and you take today off?
What are you up to?

329
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:23,370
I'm trying to find the person
who made the false accusation.

330
00:24:23,970 --> 00:24:25,700
What? Why you?

331
00:24:26,770 --> 00:24:28,140
The police are on it now.

332
00:24:29,510 --> 00:24:32,480
She acts tough, but I can tell
she's really torn up inside.

333
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:35,880
So I want to catch him
as soon as I can.

334
00:24:37,410 --> 00:24:38,420
I'm hanging up.

335
00:24:51,900 --> 00:24:55,270
I hate this feeling
of being one step behind.

336
00:24:56,270 --> 00:24:58,970
If I'm going to be the one
to catch him first...

337
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:23,160
Where's my money?

338
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:26,000
Follow me.

339
00:25:44,510 --> 00:25:45,550
Are you kidding me?

340
00:25:55,930 --> 00:25:57,830
This is what you get
for doing bad things.

341
00:26:25,590 --> 00:26:27,060
I did what you asked.

342
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:28,960
Is that so?

343
00:26:31,130 --> 00:26:32,130
Then,

344
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:34,230
we should finalize our deal.

345
00:26:34,500 --> 00:26:36,200
Finish your part first.

346
00:26:36,870 --> 00:26:39,640
The shares come after that.

347
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:42,270
What if you change your mind?

348
00:26:42,340 --> 00:26:44,340
You've got that video of me,
don't you?

349
00:26:46,940 --> 00:26:50,150
So stop worrying about me
and just do your job right.

350
00:26:51,750 --> 00:26:52,750
Ms. Choi.

351
00:26:53,750 --> 00:26:55,950
That's quite an attitude
for someone asking a favor.

352
00:26:58,320 --> 00:27:00,720
This isn't a favor. It's business.

353
00:27:00,990 --> 00:27:01,990
Even so,

354
00:27:03,260 --> 00:27:07,300
you shouldn't be so cocky
when I'm the one holding your leash.

355
00:27:08,700 --> 00:27:10,730
In this deal, I call the shots.

356
00:27:11,530 --> 00:27:12,700
Know your place.

357
00:27:39,630 --> 00:27:41,430
(BIT Life, President Kim Myung Hui)

358
00:27:51,980 --> 00:27:53,940
I just dropped Mrs. Han off.

359
00:27:54,410 --> 00:27:56,280
Right. Thanks for that.

360
00:28:00,050 --> 00:28:01,580
Why are you watching this again?

361
00:28:02,550 --> 00:28:03,920
The police are already
investigating.

362
00:28:06,190 --> 00:28:07,560
Something's still bothering me.

363
00:28:08,060 --> 00:28:11,130
After all, the thief is someone
inside the Adele Group.

364
00:28:12,630 --> 00:28:16,470
If it's one of Oh Jung Ran's people,
they might be up to something else.

365
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:19,940
Have you noticed anything unusual
since the investigation started?

366
00:28:20,970 --> 00:28:23,170
Chairman Park is taking
the investigation very seriously,

367
00:28:23,740 --> 00:28:26,180
but Oh Jung Ran couldn't seem
to care less.

368
00:28:27,410 --> 00:28:28,510
Besides,

369
00:28:30,050 --> 00:28:31,310
Ms. Choi's the suspicious one.

370
00:28:32,580 --> 00:28:35,550
- Ms. Choi?
- While we've been distracted...

371
00:28:35,550 --> 00:28:37,350
by the false accusation
and the fact...

372
00:28:37,350 --> 00:28:38,790
that Chloe
looks like Dr. Baek's daughter,

373
00:28:39,490 --> 00:28:41,290
she's been awfully quiet.

374
00:28:42,190 --> 00:28:43,330
She's the type...

375
00:28:43,330 --> 00:28:46,230
to badger you and the chairman
and make a fuss over the wedding.

376
00:28:46,830 --> 00:28:48,700
That's more like her.

377
00:29:13,590 --> 00:29:15,290
Welcome, Director Kim.

378
00:29:15,490 --> 00:29:16,960
I mean, President Kim.

379
00:29:17,830 --> 00:29:19,560
Nice of you to finally show up.

380
00:29:19,560 --> 00:29:21,160
That whole mess was ages ago.

381
00:29:22,230 --> 00:29:23,230
I apologize.

382
00:29:23,830 --> 00:29:25,770
I was held up by something
at the office.

383
00:29:26,700 --> 00:29:28,400
We heard about it on the news.

384
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:30,770
You must be so devastated.

385
00:29:30,770 --> 00:29:32,480
Devastated? Please.

386
00:29:32,840 --> 00:29:34,580
She's not the one
who had her engagement called off.

387
00:29:35,450 --> 00:29:38,410
I wanted to talk to Ms. Choi
about the wedding,

388
00:29:39,450 --> 00:29:41,550
but she must've left early
since she wasn't at her desk.

389
00:29:42,320 --> 00:29:45,360
Really? She hasn't come home yet.

390
00:29:45,560 --> 00:29:46,790
Let me give her a call.

391
00:29:47,190 --> 00:29:48,190
In that case,

392
00:29:49,690 --> 00:29:52,630
do you mind if I wait in her room
until she gets back?

393
00:29:53,360 --> 00:29:56,400
Excuse me?
You mean, in Yu Na's room?

394
00:30:04,240 --> 00:30:05,340
Of course.

395
00:30:05,340 --> 00:30:08,040
That would be better
for everyone, yes.

396
00:30:08,910 --> 00:30:09,910
This way, please.

397
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:17,390
For goodness' sake.

398
00:30:19,890 --> 00:30:20,890
Oh, dear.

399
00:30:27,460 --> 00:30:28,460
Goodness.

400
00:30:29,370 --> 00:30:32,100
Please wait here for a moment.

401
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:34,740
I'll go get you some fruit.

402
00:30:35,770 --> 00:30:36,770
Honey.

403
00:30:38,070 --> 00:30:39,840
Could you get some fruit ready?

404
00:31:18,250 --> 00:31:19,820
What do you think you're doing?

405
00:32:02,430 --> 00:32:05,500
(Pearl in Red)

406
00:32:05,760 --> 00:32:07,530
So Ms. Choi's the one
who started all this?

407
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:08,970
I had a hunch, and I was right.

408
00:32:08,970 --> 00:32:10,530
What will you do about Choi Yu Na?

409
00:32:10,600 --> 00:32:13,040
Why can't you just step in
and catch the thief yourself?

410
00:32:13,140 --> 00:32:15,740
Isn't it best to punish whoever is
responsible as soon as possible?

411
00:32:15,910 --> 00:32:17,840
We'll back the thief
into a corner first.

412
00:32:17,840 --> 00:32:20,140
We'll have time to punish
whoever is responsible later.

413
00:32:20,280 --> 00:32:22,310
You can't just show up
at work like this.

414
00:32:22,410 --> 00:32:24,210
If you try anything
and drag your feet,

415
00:32:24,210 --> 00:32:26,420
I'll tell the chairman
as soon as he's off work.

416
00:32:26,520 --> 00:32:29,490
So stop scheming and get to work.

417
00:32:30,350 --> 00:32:32,360
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
